<TITLE> Delwar faction receives revised dialogue invitation letter </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 20 (bdnews24.com)A BNP faction led by Khandaker Delwar Hossain Tuesday received a revised letter of invitation for dialogue from the government after it addressed him as secretary general, a party leader said. A special messenger from the Chief Adviser's Office reached the letter to Delwar's Sangsad Bhaban NAM flat around 3pm. BNP's acting office secretary Rizvi Ahmed told bdnews24.com: "I have received the letter on behalf of Khandaker Delwar as it invited him as secretary general of BNP." Earlier on Monday, the pro-Delwar BNP sent back the government invitation for dialogue as it had not addressed Delwar as BNP secretary general. bdnew
